==German==
===Etymology===
From [[Middle High German]] ''[[buochstap]]'', from [[Old High German]] ''[[buohstab]]'' ("letter", "writing").  From Proto-Germanic ''bōkastabaz'' ("letter"), from [[Proto-Indo-European'' roots ''*b<sup>h</sup>agós'' ("book") + ''*stěb<sup>h</sup>'', ''stemb'' ("support", "stamp", "be astonished").
===Noun===
'''Buchstabe''' {{m}} (Plural: ''Buchstaben'')
# a [[letter]] (of the alphabet)


